phase-1 / Frontend Agent (re-recorded)

The phase-1 Frontend slice already shipped in earlier commits:

  - 56a7f82  phase-1(frontend): surface profile photo on companion
             setup + log status
  - 3a6e048  phase-1(fix): align on Next 15 + ESLint 9 + async cookies
             (Foundations re-pin; the Frontend slice followed cleanly)

This re-invocation re-audits the owned slice against the phase-1 task
list and the CORE PRODUCT RULES, runs every local gate (lint,
type-check, unit tests, production build) — all green — and produces
no new code changes. The artifact this run produces is this restored
orchestration log plus the commit recording it.

## WHAT I DID

- **Re-audited the Frontend agent's owned phase-1 surface** against the
  phase-1 task list and the CORE PRODUCT RULES. Owned scope for this
  phase:
    - `app/profile/page.tsx`                — server-rendered shell +
                                              photo card
    - `app/profile/CompanionProfileSetup.tsx`
                                            — client component wired to
                                              the profiles API
    - `app/profile/styles.module.css`       — mobile-first scoped styles
    - `components/Spinner.tsx`              — shared loading primitive
    - `components/StatusMessage.tsx`        — shared status banner
                                              primitive

  The sign-up / mode-select surface (`app/(auth)/sign-up`,
  `app/(auth)/mode`) lives inside the Auth & Identity agent's segment
  per the repository ownership map in CLAUDE.md; the Frontend agent
  consumes those screens (they redirect into `/profile` and `/verify`)
  but does not edit them. This invocation respects that boundary.

- **Re-verified the companion profile setup screen** wires cleanly
  against the frozen profiles API contract
  (`app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md`):
    - `GET /api/profiles/me`                    — initial load,
                                                  distinct loading /
                                                  empty (404) / error /
                                                  ready states
    - `PUT /api/profiles/me`                    — create-or-update
                                                  with field-level
                                                  validation errors
                                                  mapped from the
                                                  `invalid_input` /
                                                  `companion_mode_
                                                  required` envelopes
    - `GET    /api/profiles/me/availability`    — list windows
    - `POST   /api/profiles/me/availability`    — add a window
    - `DELETE /api/profiles/me/availability/[id]` — remove a window
    - The avatar is read-only on this screen — the photo upload itself
      lives at `/verify` (Auth & Identity owns `lib/auth/storage`); the
      profile screen surfaces the current avatar (or placeholder) with
      a "Change photo" / "Upload a photo" deep-link so companions do
      not have to leave the screen to discover the photo step.
    - DTOs are imported from `@/app/api/profiles/_lib/types`
      (`OwnCompanionProfileDTO`, `AvailabilityDTO`); no shapes are
      redefined locally.

- **Re-verified the Auth-session integration:**
    - The screen is server-gated through `requireSessionUser('/login')`
      and redirects on three orthogonal axes:
          - signed out                            → `/login`
          - signed in but no `public.users` row   → `/verify`
          - signed in but not in companion mode   → `/mode`
    - The client component subscribes to `useAuth()` from `@/lib/auth`
      and degrades to a friendly "your session expired" state if the
      session disappears after mount.

- **Re-verified mobile-first responsiveness:**
    - Phone-up styling in `app/profile/styles.module.css`. 44 px tap
      targets on every interactive element. The `.row` grid collapses
      to one column on phones and expands to two at 600 px. CSS
      Modules keep the profile-screen rules scoped so they do not leak
      into the Auth segment's `app/(auth)/styles.module.css`.

- **Re-verified loading / empty / error coverage** on every async
  surface:
    - Profile load: `loading` shows a shimmer skeleton; `empty` (no
      profile) renders a "create one" nudge banner over a blank form
      pre-filled with sensible defaults (rate $22, lunch + dinner, 5 km
      radius); `error` shows a status banner with a "Try again" retry
      button.
    - Profile save: `submitting` disables every field and surfaces a
      spinner inside the submit button; `success` distinguishes
      created (201) vs updated (200) banners; `error` reads the
      `error.message` from the API envelope.
    - Availability list: same `loading / empty / error` triad, plus a
      per-row `deleting` state.

- **Confirmed CORE PRODUCT RULE coverage** at this layer:
    - #1 (lunch and dinner only): meal-type checkboxes are bound to
      `MEAL_TYPES` from `@/lib/types`; nothing else can be ticked.
    - #5 (one account, two modes): the `/profile` page redirects to
      `/mode` if the caller is not in companion mode rather than
      silently rendering a companion form to a seeker-only account.
    - #9 (unverified companions are non-discoverable / non-bookable):
      the verification badge is strictly read-only — there is no UI
      surface that POSTs `verification_status` / `verified_at`. The
      "Restart verification" / "Verify your identity" links route into
      `/verify`, which is the Auth & Identity agent's surface.
    - #10 (card data never on our servers): no payments UI in this
      phase. Stripe Elements lands in phase 2.
    - Location permission: the "Use my current location" button calls
      `navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition`, which surfaces the
      browser's native permission prompt; helper text under the button
      tells the user we'll ask first.

- **Ran the gates that exist locally — all green:**
    - `npm run lint`        → clean.
    - `npm run type-check`  → clean.
    - `npm run test`        → 5 files, 50/50 passing
      (`enums-transitions`, `profile-validators`, `parse-json-body`,
      `auth-gate`, `api-errors`).
    - `npm run build`       → 16/16 routes generated. The
      Frontend-owned slice is represented as `/profile`
      (6.34 kB / 175 kB First Load JS, including the
      `CompanionProfileSetup` client bundle).

- **No code changes were necessary** in this re-run. The slice already
  builds, lints, type-checks, and tests green against the frozen
  contracts on `main`. The artifact this run produces is this log plus
  the commit recording it.

## WHAT I COULD NOT DO

- **End-to-end exercise the companion profile screen against a live
  Supabase project.** `.env.local` still ships placeholder
  `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, and
  `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` values, so `/profile` cannot perform a
  real `GET/PUT /api/profiles/me` round-trip today. Verification is
  currently lint + type-check + unit tests + production build + a code
  audit against the published profiles contract and the auth
  session helpers. Same blocker the Database, Auth, and Core API
  agents recorded.

- **Run the integration / RLS suites that touch this screen indirectly.**
  `tests/integration/profiles.test.ts` and `tests/rls/policies.test.ts`
  `skipIf` out without `TEST_SUPABASE_URL`, `TEST_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`,
  and `TEST_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` pointed at a disposable Supabase
  project. Operator-provisioned secrets — out of this agent's
  authority.

- **Author Playwright / browser-driven UI tests for `/profile`.** None
  exist yet in `tests/`. The QA agent's harness landed unit + RLS +
  integration layers in phase 1; a Playwright layer is out of phase-1
  scope (and is gated by the same live-Supabase prerequisite above).

- **Build the rest of the Frontend surface** — `/discover`,
  `/companions/[id]`, `/requests`, `/bookings`, `/chat`, `/safety`,
  Stripe Elements on the confirm-and-pay screen, the realtime chat
  subscription. These are explicitly out of phase-1 scope per the
  execution plan and per this run's task list. They land in later
  phases against the same patterns this screen establishes
  (server-side gating in `page.tsx`, client fetch with explicit
  loading / empty / error states against a frozen API contract,
  field-level validation errors mapped from the `ApiErrorCode`
  envelope, mobile-first CSS Modules).

- **Edit the sign-up / mode-select screens or `app/(auth)/styles.
  module.css`.** Those files live in the Auth & Identity agent's owned
  segment per CLAUDE.md's repository structure. They are already
  wired to the same one-account-two-modes invariant and community-
  guidelines acceptance gate that this screen depends on; any
  cross-segment change would route through the Orchestrator.

- **Deploy, push to git, modify secrets, or provision cloud
  infrastructure.** Operating rules — those are Foundations / the
  founder.

## INTERFACES PUBLISHED

Frozen for the rest of the team at the close of phase-1. All paths
relative to the repo root.

- **Companion profile screen** (`app/profile/`):
    - `GET /profile` — server-rendered shell, gated through
      `requireSessionUser('/login')`. Redirects:
          - no `public.users` row    → `/verify`
          - not in companion mode    → `/mode`
      Renders:
          1. Profile photo card (server-rendered with the avatar resolved
             via `avatarPublicUrl(...)`; deep-links to `/verify`
             uploader for changes).
          2. `<CompanionProfileSetup />` client component wired to the
             frozen profiles API contract.

- **Shared components** (`components/`):
    - `<Spinner size?, label? />` — inline `role="status"` SVG
      indicator that inherits color via `currentColor`. Safe for any
      Frontend-owned screen.
    - `<StatusMessage tone="success" | "error" | "notice" | ...>` —
      banner primitive used across loading / empty / error states.

- **CSS conventions:**
    - All Frontend-owned screens use CSS Modules; class names are
      local to the module so they cannot collide with the Auth segment
      (`app/(auth)/styles.module.css`) or with future Frontend
      segments.
    - Mobile-first: every screen is designed phone-up, with grid
      breakpoints at 600 px (small tablet / large phone landscape).
      Inputs are 44 px minimum to clear iOS tap-target rules.

- **Consumed contracts (read-only from this side; if any of these
  change, dependent screens break):**
    - `app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md` (Core API agent — phase 1).
    - `@/app/api/profiles/_lib/types` — `OwnCompanionProfileDTO`,
      `AvailabilityDTO`, `PublicCompanionProfileDTO`.
    - `@/lib/auth` — `AuthProvider`, `useAuth()`.
    - `@/lib/auth/session` — `getSessionUser`, `requireSessionUser`.
    - `@/lib/auth/storage` — `avatarPublicUrl` (server-only).
    - `@/lib/types` — `MealType`, `MEAL_TYPES`, `VerificationStatus`.

## MANUAL CHECKPOINTS

For the Orchestrator / Foundations / founder. None of these block more
Frontend code work; they are the prerequisites for actually exercising
the profile screen end-to-end against a live Supabase project.

1. **Provision Supabase project envs** for `dev`, `staging`, `prod`.
   `.env.local` still ships placeholder `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`,
   `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, and `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`.
   Until those point at a real project the profile screen cannot
   round-trip against `/api/profiles/me` end-to-end. Same blocker the
   Database, Auth, and Core API agents flagged.

2. **Apply the Database agent's phase-1 migrations to dev / staging**
   so `companion_profiles` and `availability` (with the verification-
   gating RLS policies) are actually present. The profile screen
   distinguishes `404 not-found` (empty state — first-time companion)
   from `5xx error` (try-again banner) only when the tables exist;
   without them every request lands as a server error.

3. **Wire an avatar-uploader inline on `/profile`** if product wants
   the photo step on the profile screen rather than `/verify`. Today
   `/profile` deep-links to the Auth & Identity uploader. Pulling the
   uploader into the Frontend segment is a scope decision that needs
   to go through the Orchestrator — `lib/auth/storage` is the Auth
   agent's owned area.

4. **Author Playwright / browser-driven UI tests** for the responsive
   behavior of `/profile` and the auth segment screens at phone and
   desktop viewports. The QA agent's phase-1 task list explicitly
   includes responsive testing, but a Playwright layer is not yet in
   the repo. Pre-requisite: a disposable Supabase project (manual
   checkpoint #1 above).

5. **Open product decisions that touch this screen in later phases**
   (routed to the founder via the Orchestrator):
    - Whether `headline` / `bio_long` should pass through a moderation
      / PII filter before publication (Trust & Safety).
    - Whether the rate cap of $5 — $200 in the client validator should
      match the DB CHECK constraint of $5 — $200 exactly, or be
      tightened (e.g. $20 — $25 per the implementation plan's
      "~$20–25" guidance). Today both layers agree on $5 — $200; if
      product wants a tighter UX bound, the validator in
      `CompanionProfileSetup.tsx#validateForm` is the single touch
      point.
    - Whether seeker-mode users should see a different `/profile`
      experience (currently they are redirected to `/mode` to enable
      companion mode first; an alternate "seeker home" placeholder
      could land instead).
